# Data Architecture Rules

Full reference: `data-architecture.md`. This is the enforceable contract.

## STOP and notify on data-architecture changes

Before editing anything that **adds, removes, changes, reshapes, or re-ports
data** — the registries in `src/data.ts`, the `DataSource` seam, the Forge
snapshots/engine (`src/lib/forge/**`), data types in `src/types.ts`, or how data
flows into `AppState` — proactively tell the user:

> "Heads up: this touches the data architecture (`data-architecture.md`). Here's
> what changes and why."

Then keep `data-architecture.md` (and this rule) in sync in the **same** change.
Don't silently restructure data or break the single-source-of-truth / seam
contracts below.

## Single source of truth

- `TICKERS` (company facts) and   `PORTFOLIOS[].holdings` (holding facts) in
  `src/data.ts` are authoritative. **Derive, don't duplicate.** Optional
  `Portfolio.cashAvailable` is settled cash for Current Watch running totals —
  editable on portfolio sources via `updatePortfolioCash` (not watchlists).
- `INITIAL_WATCHLIST`, `TICKER_ANALYSIS`, `LOG_ENTRIES`, `DEFAULT_ASSIGNMENTS`,
  and `POSITIONS` are **derived** — never hand-edit them; edit the registries.
- Keep derivation transforms (e.g. `watchlistFromHoldings()`) **pure**.
- `ALLOCATIONS`, `RISK_RULES`, `PORTFOLIO_METRICS` are intentionally hand-authored
  literals for now (see the reference doc). Don't "fix" them into derived values
  without explicit instruction — it changes displayed numbers.

## All seeded sources unless the user scopes

Any change to portfolio/watchlist seed, `appliedPortfolioIds`, scoring filters,
edit-mode data paths, quotes/fills, or forge apply must cover **every**
`PORTFOLIOS` entry (and the same pattern for session/API sources). Never
hand-seed only `deric` / `PORTFOLIOS[0]`. Prefer derive-from-holdings
(`portfolioIdsReferencingStrategy`). If scope is ambiguous, **stop and ask** —
default is all.

Prefer a derived helper over parallel hand-maintained apply lists so new seeded
sources cannot be forgotten. Invariant:
`assertAppliedPortfoliosCoverHoldings` — every `holdings[].strategyId` must be
covered by that strategy's `appliedPortfolioIds` for the same source.

## The DataSource seam (`src/lib/datasource/`)

- Components and `AppState` must read **live/portfolio data** through
  `dataSource` (from `../lib/datasource`) — never by importing live-data
  constants (`POSITIONS`, `ALLOCATIONS`, `RISK_RULES`, `PORTFOLIO_METRICS`,
  `MARKET_FLOW`, `TICKER_ANALYSIS`, `PORTFOLIOS`, `INITIAL_WATCHLIST`,
  `LOG_ENTRIES`, `DEFAULT_ASSIGNMENTS`) straight from `src/data.ts`.
- **Static configuration / reference content** (strategy catalog, profile option
  lists, `DEFAULT_CAPTAIN`, education cards, ships/badges, score copy) is NOT
  behind the seam — import it directly from `src/data.ts`.
- Adding a new live-data accessor → add it to the `DataSource` interface AND
  `mockDataSource`.

## Going live (Pass 2 — FreeTier)

- Active binding: `freeTierDataSource` in `src/lib/datasource/index.ts`.
  Paid/brokerage later swaps the same export — don't scatter `fetch()` into UI.
- Live fields (quotes, fundies, techs, market context, Weather, search) go through
  Worker `/api/market/*` → KV-published market cycle → atomic `liveCache` commit
  → FreeTier. Authenticated clients register up to 40 symbols each (800 active
  symbols globally). Login/manual refresh never fan out upstream for steady-state
  cadence. Setup has scoped exceptions: add-ticker requests one quote for
  immediate P&L (score remains pending); apply/update/Forge Preview runs one
  debounced first check for that strategy's tickers; login also pulls missing
  book quotes and one first check per unstamped applied strategy when the cron
  cycle is still warming, preferring a completed cycle before the existing
  Worker quote/fundamental/technical routes.
- Quarantined: `TOP_SEARCH_TICKERS`, static `MARKET_CONTEXT`, `weather/mock` —
  mockDataSource / fixtures only. Live search = `asyncSearchTickers`.
- Cadence: Worker cron shards an hourly global sweep below Free-plan external
  subrequest/Yahoo soft limits and publishes only completed cycles. Check offers
  1h/2h/4h/Daily/Weekly/Monthly plus a multi-select of 4 session closes.
  **15m/30m disabled** ("Future Capability"); 1h is the data floor. Checks run
  for applied strategies regardless of `cadenceEnabled`; that field now controls
  the **Enable Notifications** preference only.
- Layer 1 coverage: `liveCoverage.ts` / Forge dropdowns / default strategies.
  Layer 2: null = no-data. Layer 3: `NeedsDataReviewFlag` for critical gaps.
  Timeframed technicals: Worker computes comprehensive-core indicators from one
  closed Yahoo 1h OHLCV series per ticker, resampled locally to
  2h/4h/1D/1W/1M. Sub-hour legacy chips migrate to 1h; invalid stragglers score
  no-data.
  Excluded (no honest free source): `interestCoverage`, `dividendGrowth5yPct`,
  `buybackYieldPct`. Never fabricate a value to widen coverage.

## Market Weather (`src/lib/weather/`)

- Scoring (`scoring.ts`) is **pure and provider-agnostic** — feed it normalized
  0–100 sub-scores via `buildReading()`. Don't hand-build readings in the UI.
- Condition metadata (labels, colors, icons, copy) lives ONLY in
  `conditions.ts`; per-condition CSS is `.weather--<id>` / `.weather-bg--<id>`.
- Read weather through `dataSource.getMarketWeather(timeframe)`, never by
  importing `weather/mock.ts` from a component.
- FreeTier: `weather/live.ts` builds from live `MarketContext` (Worker FRED +
  index ETFs). Sector/industry keys come from `weather/taxonomy.ts` (GICS 11 /
  74); `TICKERS[].sector`/`.industry` must use those exact keys for cascade.
  Live holdings map via Yahoo `assetProfile` on the existing fundamentals
  `quoteSummary` (`yahooTaxonomy.ts`) — never fabricate IT/Software. Watch
  stocks are augmented client-side (`getWatchMarketWeather`); gaps upsert
  `taxonomy_gap_events`. Snapshot covers the full taxonomy so users can browse
  weather without holdings. Cache app-wide per timeframe until context
  refreshes. See `data-architecture.md` §5.
- **Beta 0 user data:** Supabase Auth + Postgres RLS (`user_state`,
  `conviction_snapshots`, `portfolio_snapshots`, `ticker_marks`). Not
  localStorage SoT. `ticker_marks` hydrates account last prices into
  `liveCache`; `flags.lastDataPullAtByStrategyId` hydrates successful strategy
  check stamps. Marks never make conviction ready without a stamp. Successful
  setup/cron reads upsert both so local and deployed clients match for the same
  account; their Worker KV stores remain separate. Invite codes + Admin role.
  See `supabase/schema.sql` and `src/lib/userStore/`. `flags.badgeToastsSeen`
  = one-shot Helm onboarding-badge toast IDs; `flags.weatherReaderLayers`
  = Market/Sector/Industry/Stock detail opens for Weather Reader; earn state
  stays derived (`onboardingBadges.ts`). Manual cash deposit/withdrawal ledger
  rows + `portfolio_snapshots.metrics.cashAdded` / `cashWithdrawn` (same-day
  cash ledger sums) support Cash Added over Time; qty-driven cash is not a
  cash ledger row.

## Strategy Forge (`src/lib/forge/`)

- The scoring engine (`scoring.ts`) is **pure, no I/O** — it takes a strategy +
  a `MetricContext` and returns conviction. Display labels come from
  `status.ts` (`resolveStatus`: Layer 1 conviction band + Layer 2 category
  diagnostics → `ResolvedStatus`). Layer 3 zone overlays (Trim Zone / Add Zone /
  Go to Cash) are registered on `StatusType`; authoring uses
  `strategy.trimZone*` / `addZone*` / `goToCash*` rules+tags (not scored).
  Zones fire via `evaluateZoneFlags` (any active chip fail) into
  `resolveStatus` (`zoneFlags` / `zoneSurface`). Don't
  fetch or import data inside scoring;
  feed it through `alignment.ts`, which reads the `dataSource` seam.
- Forge inputs come **through the seam**: `getFundamentals`, `getTechnicals`,
  `getMarketContext`, `getBuckets`. A missing metric is `null` ("no data"),
  never a fabricated value. Snapshot values must be **real, sourced** figures
  (last close + latest reported fundamentals) carrying `asOf` + `source`.
- The **metric registry** (`metrics.ts`) is the single source of truth for what
  a chip can test. Add a metric = add to `MetricKey` (`types.ts`) + seed the
  snapshot (`data.ts`) + register in `metrics.ts` **and** add a Free Tier
  sanity bound (or explicit “no bound”) in `metricSanity.ts` / Worker twin.
  Nothing else.
- Scoring follows the normalized tag/chip/weight algorithm in
  `docs/strategy-forge.md`: active chips (tag-lens union, deduped) → pass/fail
  → rule weights renormalized to 100% of the category → `categoryScore ×
  categoryWeight` summed. **No** thesis/risk gates or conviction clamps.
  Rule weights, tag weights, and category weights each sum to 100;
  `validateStrategy` completeness gates "Apply to Portfolio".
- Conviction is **market-value-weighted** across bucket allocations; a ticker's
  headline = its best-aligned bucket. `AppState` overlays computed
  conviction/status/resolved onto the watchlist — downstream chips (`StatusStack`,
  `PortfolioCompass`) reflect it. "Notify" = in-app chips updating; **no**
  push-notification system.
- The Helm progress metrics (`HelmMetrics` + pure `forge/helmMetrics.ts`) live
  tiles are a **pure read** of alignment — no scoring change. Portfolio mirrors
  Current Watch via `selectedPortfolioId` (display-only; not in `user_state`);
  strategy scope is shared Home UI state `watchStrategyScopeId` (null = All;
  Forge preview local only). Single-strategy scope filters every Progress metric
  (incl. Open P&L) via `tickerInScope` / `shouldScoreTickerWithStrategy`.
  **Conviction Change** uses `metrics.conviction` on book snapshots + ticker
  `conviction_snapshots` for drivers (no fabricated history). **Open P&L
  sparkline** reads additive `portfolio_snapshots` (`strategy_id ''` = whole
  book; cash on every scope). Write path: `persistBookAndConvictionMarks` after
  **Open P&L sparkline** reads additive `portfolio_snapshots` (`strategy_id ''` =
  whole book; cash on every scope). Write path: `persistBookAndConvictionMarks`
  after live refresh — `as_of` is America/New_York market session day (capped to
  Last Conviction Check on non-check writes so Open P&L cannot invent a spark day
  ahead of the toast); Open P&L upserts on that day, but `metrics.conviction`
  stamps only on check days (or check-driven writes); enriches ticker conviction
  payload; does **not** change Forge / zone / `portfolioRunningTotals` math. Also
  writes `metrics.cashAdded` / `cashWithdrawn` from same-day cash ledger rows.
  Check-driven path also appends `forge_check_events` (status + hold-inaction)
  for Plan Adherence. Editable portfolio cash (`updatePortfolioCash`) +
  `PortfolioTransaction` ledger in `share_fills` (qty + cash; cash rows are
  manual deposit/withdrawal only).
- Cadence: Check = 1h/2h/4h/Daily/Weekly/Monthly + any combination of 4
  intraday session-closes. **15m/30m disabled** ("Future Capability");
  fundamentals refresh daily through the cron cycle. Checks are core behavior;
  `cadenceEnabled` is notifications-only and email/text/browser are placeholders.
  See `data-architecture.md` §6. Cadence / cron / KV publish stay unchanged;
  chip pass/fail is stamp-aligned (see `docs/strategy-forge.md` Pass/fail audit
  contract). `openPnlPct` for chips is mark × avg at score time; Free Tier
  fundies pass through `metricSanity` (absurd → null / no-data). Incomplete
  published cycles (missing context or ticker fundamentals) stay Score Pending.

## Safety

- All data is static mock placeholder. Before introducing real/realistic
  personal or financial data, follow `.cursor/rules/security-hardening.mdc`.
